Skip Mix profiler tests on Solaris.

The Erlang profiler trace setup can hang on Solaris.  On SPARC this leaves the
Mix test runner stuck in :erlang.trace_pattern/3 long enough for BOB to time
out the test phase, and a timed-out profiler test can leave the Mix tmp
directory busy enough for later cleanup to fail with EINVAL.

--- elixir-1.20.1/lib/mix/test/mix/tasks/profile.cprof_test.exs
+++ elixir-1.20.1/lib/mix/test/mix/tasks/profile.cprof_test.exs
@@ -10,6 +10,10 @@ defmodule Mix.Tasks.Profile.CprofTest do
   import ExUnit.CaptureIO
   alias Mix.Tasks.Profile.Cprof
 
+  if :os.type() == {:unix, :sunos} do
+    @moduletag skip: "Erlang profiler trace setup hangs on Solaris"
+  end
+
   @expr "Enum.each(1..5, &String.Chars.Integer.to_string/1)"
 
   test "profiles evaluated expression", context do
